  <h1>
   path_scale
  </h1>
  This value can be used to get or to set the scale of the currently assigned path for the instance (as set by the function
  <span>
   <a href="../path_start.htm">
    path_start()
   </a>
  </span>
  )Â with a default value of 1. This is a scalar value, so
    1 is a scale of 1:1, while setting it to 2, for example, will be double the scale and setting it to 0.5 would be halving the scale.
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">path_scale;
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Overview/Data_Types.htm">
 Real
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">path_scale = 1 + random(2);
</code></pre>
  The above code will set the current path's scale to a random size between 1 (its original size) and 3 (3 times its original size).
 </body>
